						<summary>

						<p>The inscription states that the throne in the <hi rend="italic">paḷḷi-aṟai</hi> of god Kālakāladēvar is the gift of one Tiruvālavāychchokkaṉ, a resident of Neḍunduḷadi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Rājamārttāṇḍanallūr in Tuvvūr-kūṟṟam a division of Pāṇḍimaṇḍalam.</p>						

